            title: "Conduct a Money Script Audit",
            description: "Set aside an hour to write honestly about your earliest memories involving money — what your parents said about it, what the emotional atmosphere was around financial topics, any significant financial events from childhood. Then write out the beliefs about money you carry now: what rich people are like, whether you deserve financial security, what money does to relationships. These autobiographical exercises surface the money scripts that are currently running in the background of your financial life. You cannot change what you cannot see."
          },
