            title: "Develop a Money Conversation Practice",
            description: "One of the most powerful things you can do for your financial psychology is to break the taboo of financial discussion. Find one trusted person — a partner, a close friend, a financial therapist — and make money conversations a regular practice. Research by Brad Klontz and others consistently finds that bringing money beliefs into explicit conversation accelerates the process of challenging and changing them. The shame that makes financial avoidance so costly dissolves fastest in the presence of non-judgmental disclosure."
          }
        ]} />
